# Verification — use check scripts, not CI polling

CI (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`) runs:

- `./scripts/check-go.sh --lint-only --verbose`
- `./scripts/check-go.sh --tests-only --group=<core|tasks|agents|harness> --verbose` (matrix)
- `./scripts/check-web.sh --install --verbose`

Those are wrapped by **`scripts/check.sh`** (Unix) and **`scripts/check.ps1`** (Windows). Run the local check script to verify the same bar CI enforces.

## Do

- Before finishing or pushing: run **`./scripts/check.sh`** from repo root (or **`.\scripts\check.ps1`** on Windows).
- First web run or lockfile change: add **`--install`** / **`-Install`**.
- Scoped iteration: **`--go-only`** / **`-GoOnly`** or **`--web-only`** / **`-WebOnly`**.
- No local Go/Node: **`docker compose run --rm dev ./scripts/check.sh --install`** ([docs/docker.md](../docs/docker.md)).
- Fix failures from check output locally, then re-run check until green.

## Do not

- Do **not** use **`gh run watch`**, repeated **`gh run list`**, or poll Actions as the primary verification loop — it is slow and redundant.
- Do **not** re-run individual CI steps ad hoc (`go test ./...`, `npm test`, funclogmeasure) unless narrowing a failure **after** check failed, or the user asked for a subset.
- Use **`gh run view --log-failed`** only when check passed locally but CI still failed (environment drift).

## Quick reference

| Platform | Full bar | Go only |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Unix / Git Bash / Docker dev | `./scripts/check.sh` | `./scripts/check.sh --go-only` |
| Windows PowerShell | `.\scripts\check.ps1` | `.\scripts\check.ps1 -GoOnly` |

